id: agent_eval
definitions:
  targetNamespace: http://bpmn.io/schema/bpmn
  xmlns:bpmn: http://www.omg.org/spec/BPMN/20100524/MODEL
  xmlns:studyflow: http://behaverse.org/schemas/studyflow/v1
  xmlns:cognitive: http://behaverse.org/schemas/studyflow/cognitive
  xmlns:exec: https://w3id.org/studyflow/exec
  xmlns:ml: https://w3id.org/studyflow/ml
  xmlns:agentic: https://w3id.org/studyflow/agentic
Agent_Eval:
  type: bpmn:Process
  documentation: |
    An agent-evaluation harness: for every item in an eval set, run a tool-using
    agent, check its output, score it, and collect the results - with a sample
    routed to human raters.

    The point of the diagram is the line down the middle of it. Everything outside
    the Agent follows a path the diagram fixes: fan out, guard, judge, collect.
    Inside the Agent, nothing does - the model picks which tool to call and when,
    and stops when it decides it is done. That is the difference between a workflow
    and an agent, and here it is the difference between a plain sub-process and an
    ad-hoc one, which is the element BPMN has always used to mean "order decided at
    run time".

    Two consequences follow from drawing it this way:

    - The agent's tools are the activities inside it. A tool that is not drawn is a
      capability nobody reviewed.
    - Every model call, tool call, and routing decision is one execution in the run
      log. A non-deterministic run is still replayable, because a replay reads the
      recorded decisions instead of asking the model again.
  extensionElements:
    - type: studyflow:Study
  name: Agent evaluation harness
  flowElements:
    Start:
      type: bpmn:StartEvent
      name: Start eval
      outgoing:
        - Flow_Start_Each
    Eval_Set:
      type: bpmn:DataStoreReference
      extensionElements:
        - type: studyflow:Dataset
      name: Eval set
    Rubric:
      type: bpmn:DataObjectReference
      extensionElements:
        - type: agentic:Prompt
          template: |
            Score the answer 1-5 on: factual support from the retrieved passages,
            completeness against the question, and absence of unsupported claims.
            A 5 requires every claim to be traceable to a passage.
      version: "3"
      name: Scoring rubric
    Per_Item:
      type: bpmn:SubProcess
      documentation: |
        One instance per item, each in its own scope with its own derived seed. The
        instances are independent, so this is also the unit of parallelism - raise
        `maxConcurrency` and it is the same diagram running wider.
      extensionElements:
        - type: exec:ForEach
      name: For each eval item
      incoming:
        - Flow_Start_Each
      outgoing:
        - Flow_Each_Agreement
      over: items
      itemVar: question
      maxConcurrency: 16
      collect: concat
      collectAs: scores
      flowElements:
        Research_Agent:
          type: bpmn:AdHocSubProcess
          documentation: |
            An ad-hoc sub-process: the model chooses which of the tools below to call,
            and how many times, until it can answer. `deterministic` is pinned false -
            the engine records each choice rather than assuming it can re-derive it.
          extensionElements:
            - type: agentic:Agent
              maxTurns: 8
              model: claude-opus-4-8
              systemPrompt: |
                Answer the question using the corpus. Search before you answer, cite
                the passages you used, and say so plainly when the corpus does not
                support an answer.
          name: Research agent
          outgoing:
            - Flow_Agent_Check
          until: answer is not null
          flowElements:
            Search:
              type: bpmn:ServiceTask
              extensionElements:
                - type: agentic:Retriever
                  index: study_corpus
                  topK: 8
                  embeddingModel: voyage-3
              name: Search corpus
            Compute:
              type: bpmn:ServiceTask
              extensionElements:
                - type: agentic:Tool
                  kind: code
                  purpose: |
                    Run a short Python snippet over the trial table to check a claim
                    numerically. Use it when the question turns on a statistic.
              name: Run analysis
              uses: python://lab.tools.analyze
        Check_Output:
          type: bpmn:ServiceTask
          extensionElements:
            - type: agentic:Guardrail
              policy: |
                Every claim in the answer must be supported by a retrieved passage.
                Reject answers that cite passages the retriever never returned.
          name: Groundedness check
          incoming:
            - Flow_Agent_Check
          outgoing:
            - Flow_Check_Score
        Score:
          type: bpmn:ServiceTask
          documentation: |
            Three independent judgements per item, taken because one judge's score is
            noise. The judge model is named on the diagram: it is part of the measuring
            instrument, and swapping it moves the numbers.
          extensionElements:
            - type: agentic:Judge
              rubric: |
                Apply the scoring rubric. Give the score and one sentence of
                justification naming the deciding criterion.
              model: claude-opus-4-8
              jurors: 3
          name: Judge answer
          incoming:
            - Flow_Check_Score
          outgoing:
            - Flow_Score_Sample
        Sample:
          type: bpmn:ExclusiveGateway
          extensionElements:
            - type: cognitive:RandomGateway
          name: Sample for human review?
          incoming:
            - Flow_Score_Sample
          outgoing:
            - Flow_Sample_Human
            - Flow_Sample_Done
        Human_Rating:
          type: bpmn:UserTask
          documentation: |
            The human half of the evaluation. Two raters per sampled item, so
            agreement between them - and between them and the model judge - is
            computable rather than assumed.
          extensionElements:
            - type: agentic:HumanFeedback
              rubric: |
                Score the answer against the same rubric the model judge used.
              scale: 1-5 Likert
              raters: 2
          name: Human rating
          incoming:
            - Flow_Sample_Human
          outgoing:
            - Flow_Human_Done
        Item_Done:
          type: bpmn:EndEvent
          name: Item scored
          incoming:
            - Flow_Sample_Done
            - Flow_Human_Done
        Flow_Agent_Check:
          type: bpmn:SequenceFlow
          sourceRef: Research_Agent
          targetRef: Check_Output
        Flow_Check_Score:
          type: bpmn:SequenceFlow
          sourceRef: Check_Output
          targetRef: Score
        Flow_Score_Sample:
          type: bpmn:SequenceFlow
          sourceRef: Score
          targetRef: Sample
        Flow_Sample_Human:
          type: bpmn:SequenceFlow
          name: sampled
          sourceRef: Sample
          targetRef: Human_Rating
        Flow_Sample_Done:
          type: bpmn:SequenceFlow
          name: not sampled
          sourceRef: Sample
          targetRef: Item_Done
        Flow_Human_Done:
          type: bpmn:SequenceFlow
          sourceRef: Human_Rating
          targetRef: Item_Done
    Agreement:
      type: bpmn:ServiceTask
      extensionElements:
        - type: ml:Evaluate
          metrics:
            - mean_judge_score
            - judge_human_agreement
            - guardrail_block_rate
          split: holdout
      name: Score the eval
      incoming:
        - Flow_Each_Agreement
      outgoing:
        - Flow_Agreement_Done
      uses: python://lab.eval.summarize
    Done:
      type: bpmn:EndEvent
      name: Eval complete
      incoming:
        - Flow_Agreement_Done
    Flow_Start_Each:
      type: bpmn:SequenceFlow
      sourceRef: Start
      targetRef: Per_Item
    Flow_Each_Agreement:
      type: bpmn:SequenceFlow
      sourceRef: Per_Item
      targetRef: Agreement
    Flow_Agreement_Done:
      type: bpmn:SequenceFlow
      sourceRef: Agreement
      targetRef: Done
